@flexiarg musn/declare-scope
@title Declare Scope and Exit Condition
@sigils [üìê/ÂÜÖ]
@audience fulab agents, musn server
@tone technical
@style pattern

! conclusion: State in-bounds scope, out-of-bounds scope, and a clear exit condition up front.
  + context: Ambiguous scope makes it hard to judge off-trail moves and completion.
  + IF:
    The agent proceeds without declaring what is in scope or when to stop.
  + HOWEVER:
    The run still needs enough flexibility to explore safely.
  + THEN:
    Require a brief scope line describing in-bounds, out-of-bounds, and exit condition.
  + BECAUSE:
    Explicit scope anchors decisions and makes pauses and audit logs legible.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: agent message contains a "Scope:" line with in/out/exit.
    - evidence-shape: {:scope {:in :string, :out :string, :exit :string}}
